Long-awaited Timaru Hospital lift set for installation
ESTHER ASHBY-COVENTRY
Last updated19:05, May 2 2016
Esther Ashby-Coventry
Painting around the lift shaft at the Timaru Hospital Gardens Block was completed in November last year but the lift still has not been installed.
Timaru Hospital might soon commissionits new liftmonths after it was meant to be installed.An installation contractor was due at the redevelopedTimaru HospitalGarden Block on Tuesday, a South Canterbury District Health board spokeswoman confirmed.Once there, the lift should take four to six weeks to install, spokeswoman Natasha Hoskins said.The confirmation followed the health board being told on Friday that the installer had not been able to install the lift last month.The installer had experienced a "mishap" so could not be there to install the lift as expected.The lift was originally scheduled to arrive in Timaru from China in October last year. It was subsequently expected to arrive by November 25.The lift finally started to arrive in piecesfrom December. That month, theboard was told thelift was shipped to Auckland and not Lyttelton, as initially believed.
